quran[357]{c,v,t}:
  36,28,"And We did not send down against his people after him any guest from heaven, nor was it necessary for Us to do so"
  36,29,"It was no more than a single mighty blast, and behold, they were gone"
  36,30,"Unfortunately for these slaves, there does not come a messenger to them that they did not mock"
  36,31,Do they not see how many generations before them We caused to perish? And they will not return to them
  36,32,But each one of them will be brought before Us
  36,33,"A sign for them is the earth that is dead. We give it life, and produce grain from it, of which you eat"
  36,34,"And We produce in it orchards with date palms and vines, and We cause springs to gush forth therein"
  36,35,That they may enjoy the fruits of it. It was not their hands that made this. Will they not then give thanks
  36,36,"Glory be to God, Who created in pairs all things that the earth produces, all of it, and things that they do not know of"
  36,37,"And a sign for them is the night. We withdraw from it the day, and behold, they are plunged into darkness"
  36,38,"And the Sun runs its course for a period determined for it. That is His decree, the Exalted in Might, the All Knowing"
  36,39,"And the Moon, We have ordained for it phases, until it returns like the withered lower part of a date-stalk"
  36,40,"It is not permitted for the Sun to catch the Moon, nor can the night outstrip the day. Each swims along in its own orbit"
  36,41,And a sign for them is that We carried their people through the flood in the loaded Ark
  36,42,And We have created for them similar vessels on which they ride
  36,43,"If it were Our will, We could drown them. Then there would be no helper, nor could they be delivered"
  36,44,"Except by way of mercy from Us, and by way of convenience for a time"
  36,45,"They are told, “Be conscious of that which is before you and that which is after you, in order that you may receive mercy.”"
  36,46,"Not a sign comes to them from among the signs of their Lord, except those from which they turn away"
  36,47,"And when they are told, “Give of that which God has provided you,” the unbelievers say to those who believe, “Shall we feed those whom if God had so willed, He would have fed Himself? You are in nothing but manifest error.”"
  36,48,"Further they say, “When will this promise come to pass, if what you say is true?”"
  36,49,They will not have to wait for anything but a single blast. It will seize them while they are still disputing among themselves
  36,50,"Then no chance will they have with their will to manage their affairs, nor to return to their people"
  36,51,"The trumpet will be sounded, when behold, from their place of rest, people will rush forth to their Lord"
  36,52,"They will say, “Woe to us, who has raised us up from our resting place?” This is what God, the Merciful Benefactor, promised. And true was the word of the messengers.”"
  36,53,"It will be no more than a single blast, and then they will all be brought up before Us"
  36,54,"Then on that day, not a soul will be wronged in the least, and you will be repaid for your past deeds"
  36,55,Indeed on that day the companions of the garden will have joy in all that they do
  36,56,"They and their mates will be in groves of shade, reclining on thrones"
  36,57,"Fruit will be there for them, they will have whatever they call for"
  36,58,"“Peace,” a word from the Lord, Mercifully Redeeming"
  36,59,"“And O you in sin, get away this day"
  36,60,"“Did I not enjoin on you, O you children of Adam, that you should not worship Satan, and that he was to you a sworn enemy"
  36,61,"“And that you should worship Me, and that this is the straight way"
  36,62,“But he led astray a great multitude of you. Did you not then use reason
  36,63,“This is the hell about which you were warned
  36,64,"“Embrace the fire this day, because you rejected it.”"
  36,65,"That day will We put a seal on their mouths, but their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will bear witness to all that they did"
  36,66,"If it had been Our will, We could surely have removed their eyes, then they would have run about grabbing for the path, but how could they have seen"
  36,67,"And if it had been Our will, We could have transformed them in their places, then they would have been unable to proceed, and they could not have returned"
  36,68,"If We grant long life to any, We cause them to be reversed in creation. Will they not then understand"
  36,69,"We have not instructed the messenger in poetry, nor is that like him. This is no less than a message and a Quran making things clear"
  36,70,"That it may give advice to any that are alive, and that the charge may be proven against those who reject it"
  36,71,"Do they not see that it is We who have created for them livestock, among the things that Our hands have fashioned that are under their control"
  36,72,"And that We have subjected them to their use? Of them, some carry them and some they eat"
  36,73,"And they obtain other benefits from them, including drink. Will they not then be grateful"
  36,74,"Yet they take for worship gods other than God, thinking that they might be helped"
  36,75,"They do not have the power to help them, but they will be brought up all together"
  36,76,But do not let their speech grieve you. Indeed We know what they hide as well as what they disclose
  36,77,"Do human beings not see that it is We Who created them from a zygote? Yet behold, he stands up as an open adversary"
  36,78,"And he makes comparisons to Us, and forgets his own origin and creation. He says, “Who can give life to bones, and decomposed ones at that?”"
  36,79,"Say, “He will give them life Who created them the first time. For He is well-versed in every kind of creation"
  36,80,"“The same One who produces for you fire out of the green tree, when behold, you kindle with it"
  36,81,"“Is not He Who created the heavens and the earth able to create the likes of him?” Yes indeed, for He is the Ultimate Creator, the All Knowing"
  36,82,"Indeed, when He intends a thing, His command is “Be”, and it is"
  36,83,"So glory be to Him in Whose hands are the control of all things, and to Him will you all be brought back"
  37,1,By those who line themselves in ranks
  37,2,And so are strong in repelling harm
  37,3,And so proclaim the message
  37,4,Indeed your God is one
  37,5,"Lord of the heavens and of the earth, and all between them, and Lord of every point at the rising of the Sun"
  37,6,We have indeed decked the lower heaven with beauty in the stars
  37,7,For beauty and to guard against all rebellious devils
  37,8,"They should not strain their ears in the direction of the exalted assembly, but shall be cast away from every side"
  37,9,"Repulsed, for they are under a perpetual penalty"
  37,10,"Except those that snatch away something by stealth, and they are pursued by a flaming fire of piercing brightness"
  37,11,"Just ask their opinion. Are they more difficult to create, or the other beings We have created? We have created them out of wet clay"
  37,12,Indeed you marvel while they ridicule
  37,13,"And though they are advised, they pay no heed"
  37,14,"And when they see a sign, they turn it into mockery"
  37,15,"And say, “This is nothing but evident deception"
  37,16,"“What, when we die and become dust and bones, will we be raised up"
  37,17,“And also our ancestors?”
  37,18,"Say, “Yes, and you will then be humiliated.”"
  37,19,"Then there will be a single cry, and behold, they will begin to see"
  37,20,"They will say, “Woe to us, this is the Day of Accountability!”"
  37,21,"This is the day of sorting out, the truth you once denied"
  37,22,"“Bring up,” it will be said, “The wrongdoers and their partners, and the things they worshipped"
  37,23,"“Besides God, and lead them to the way of the fire"
  37,24,"“But stop them, for they must be asked"
  37,25,“What is the matter with you that you did not help each other?”
  37,26,"No, but that day they will submit"
  37,27,"And they will turn to one another, and question each other"
  37,28,"They will say, “It was you who used to come to us from the right.”"
  37,29,"They will reply, “No, you yourselves had no faith"
  37,30,"“Nor had we any authority over you. No, it was you who were a people in obstinate rebellion"
  37,31,"“So now has been proved true against us, the word of our Lord, so we will indeed taste it"
  37,32,"“We led you astray, for indeed we were ourselves astray.”"
  37,33,"Indeed that day, they will all share in the penalty"
  37,34,Indeed that is how We will deal with the wrong-doers
  37,35,"For they, when they were told that there is no god except God, would puff themselves up with pride–"
  37,36,"And say, “What, will we give up our gods for the sake of a poet possessed?”"
  37,37,"No, he has come with the truth, and he confirms the messengers"
  37,38,You will indeed taste the terrible penalty
  37,39,But it will be no more than retribution for what you did
  37,40,But the sincere servants of God
  37,41,For them is sustenance determined
  37,42,"They will enjoy fruits, and honor and dignity"
  37,43,In gardens of felicity
  37,44,Facing each other on thrones
  37,45,Round will be passed to them a cup from a clear-flowing fountain
  37,46,"White, of a taste delicious to those who drink of it"
  37,47,"Free from harm, nor will they suffer intoxication from it"
  37,48,And with them will be companions of modest gaze and beautiful eyes
  37,49,Like delicate eggs closely guarded
  37,50,Then they will turn to one another and question each other
  37,51,"One of them will start the conversation by saying, “I had a friend"
  37,52,"“Who used to say, ‘What, are you among those who bear witness to the truth"
  37,53,"“When we die and become dust and bones, will we indeed receive rewards and punishments?”"
  37,54,"A voice said, “Would you like to look down?”"
  37,55,He looked down and saw him in the middle of the fire
  37,56,"He said, “By God, you were just short of bringing me to perdition"
  37,57,"“Had it not been for the grace of my Lord, I would certainly have been among those sent there"
  37,58,“Is it the case that we will not die
  37,59,"“Except our first death, and that we will not be punished?”"
  37,60,Indeed this is the greatest achievement
  37,61,For the like of this let all strive who wish to strive
  37,62,Is that the better entertainment or the Tree of Zaqqum
  37,63,For We have truly made it a trial for the wrongdoers
  37,64,For it is a tree that springs out of the bottom of hellfire
  37,65,The shoots of its fruit-stalks are like the heads of devils
  37,66,Truly they will eat of it and fill their stomachs
  37,67,Then indeed on top of that they will be given a mixture made of boiling water
  37,68,Then their return will be to the fire
  37,69,Truly they found their parents on the wrong path
  37,70,So they were rushed down on their footsteps
  37,71,"And truly before them, many of the ancients went astray"
  37,72,"But We sent among them, people to advise them"
  37,73,Then see what was the end of those who were advised
  37,74,Except the sincere servants of God
  37,75,"Noah called to Us, and We are the best to hear prayers"
  37,76,And We delivered him and his people from the Great Calamity
  37,77,And made his progeny to endure
  37,78,And We left for him generations to come in later times
  37,79,Peace and salutation to Noah among the nations
  37,80,Indeed we reward those who do right
  37,81,For he was one of our believing servants
  37,82,Then the rest we overwhelmed in the flood
  37,83,Indeed among those who followed his way was Abraham
  37,84,"Behold, he approached his Lord with a pure heart"
  37,85,"Behold, he said to his father and to his people, “What is it you worship"
  37,86,“Is it false gods instead of God that you desire
  37,87,“Then what is your idea about the Lord of the worlds?”
  37,88,Then he cast a glance at the stars
  37,89,"And he said, “I am indeed sick.”"
  37,90,"So they turned away from him, and departed"
  37,91,"Then he turned to their gods and said, “Will you not eat"
  37,92,“What is the matter with you that you do not speak?”
  37,93,"Then did he turn to them, striking them with the right hand"
  37,94,"Then they came with hurried steps, and faced him"
  37,95,"He said, “You worship that which you have carved"
  37,96,“But God has created you and that which you make.”
  37,97,"They said, “Build him a furnace, and throw him into the blazing fire.”"
  37,98,"They then sought another strategy against him, but We made them the ones most humiliated"
  37,99,"He said, “I will go to my Lord, He will surely guide me"
  37,100,"“O my Lord, grant me one from the righteous.”"
  37,101,So We gave him the good news of a child ready to sacrifice and forbear
  37,102,"Then when he reached the age of work he said, “O my son, I see in a vision that I offer you in sacrifice. Now tell me what you see?” The son said, “O my father, do as you are asked. You will find me, God willing, one practicing patience and constancy.”"
  37,103,"So when they both submitted their wills, and he laid him prostrate on his forehead"
  37,104,"We called out to him “O Abraham,”"
  37,105,“You have already fulfilled the vision.” Indeed We reward those who do right
  37,106,For this was a challenge
  37,107,And We ransomed him with a momentous sacrifice
  37,108,And We left this blessing for him among generations to come
  37,109,“Peace and salutation to Abraham.”
  37,110,Indeed We reward those who do right
  37,111,For he was one of our believing servants
  37,112,"And We gave him the good news of Isaac, a prophet, one of the righteous"
  37,113,"We blessed him and Isaac, but of their progeny are some who do right and some who do wrong, to their own souls"
  37,114,Again We bestowed Our favor on Moses and Aaron
  37,115,And We delivered them and their people from great calamity
  37,116,"And We helped them, so they overcame"
  37,117,And We gave them the Clear Books
  37,118,And We guided them to the straight way
  37,119,And We left this blessing for them among generations to come
  37,120,“Peace and salutation to Moses and Aaron.”
  37,121,So indeed We reward those who do right
  37,122,For they were two of our believing servants
  37,123,Elias was also among those sent by Us
  37,124,"Behold, he said to his people, “Will you not be conscious"
  37,125,“Will you call upon Baal and abandon the Best of Creators
  37,126,“Your Lord and the Lord of your ancestors?”
  37,127,"But they rejected him, and they will certainly be called up"
  37,128,Except the sincere and devoted servants of God
  37,129,And We left this blessing for him among generations to come
  37,130,“Peace be upon Elias.”
  37,131,Then indeed do We reward those who do right
  37,132,For he was one of our believing servants
  37,133,Lot was also among those sent by Us
  37,134,"Behold, We delivered him and all his adherents"
  37,135,Except an old woman who was among those who lagged behind
  37,136,Then We caused the rest to perish
  37,137,"Indeed you pass by their sites, by day–"
  37,138,And by night. Then will you not use reason
  37,139,Jonah was also among those sent by Us
  37,140,When he ran away to the ship fully stocked
  37,141,"He cast lots, and he was condemned"
  37,142,Then the fish swallowed him. He had done things worthy of blame
  37,143,Had it not been that he glorified God
  37,144,He would certainly have remained inside the fish until the Day of Resurrection
  37,145,But We cast him up on the naked shore in a state of sickness
  37,146,And We caused to grow over him a spreading plant of the gourd kind
  37,147,And We sent him to a hundred thousand people or more
  37,148,And they believed. So We permitted them to enjoy their time
  37,149,"Then ask them, do the females belong to God and the males to you"
  37,150,Or did you see Us create the angels female
  37,151,Is it not that they say falsely
  37,152,“God has children”? But they are liars
  37,153,Did He choose daughters over sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How judge you
  37,155,Will you not then receive advice
  37,156,Or have you an authority manifest
  37,157,Then bring your book if you are truthful
  37,158,And they have created a blood relationship between Him and the jinn. But the jinn know that they have indeed to appear
  37,159,"Glory be to God, He is free from the things they ascribe to Him"
  37,160,"Not so the servants of God, sincere and devoted"
  37,161,Indeed neither you nor those you worship
  37,162,Can lead any into temptation concerning God
  37,163,Except those whom are themselves heading to the blazing fire
  37,164,"“Not us, only for him is a place known"
  37,165,“And indeed we are arranged in ranks
  37,166,“And we are indeed those who declare God's glory.”
  37,167,And there were those who said
  37,168,“If only we had before us a message from those in the past
  37,169,"“We would certainly have been servants of God, sincere.”"
  37,170,"So they reject it, but soon will they know"
  37,171,Our word has already been passed on before to Our servants sent by Us
  37,172,So that they would certainly be assisted
  37,173,And that Our forces surely must conquer
  37,174,So turn away from them for a little while
  37,175,"And watch them, and they soon will see"
  37,176,Do they wish to rush our punishment
  37,177,"But when it descends into the open space before them, terrible will be the morning for those who were warned"
  37,178,So turn away from them for a little while
  37,179,And watch and they soon will see
  37,180,"Glory to your Lord, the Lord of Honor and Power, free from what they ascribe to Him"
  37,181,And peace on the messengers
  37,182,"And praise God, the Guardian Evolver of all the worlds"
  38,1,"Saad. By the Quran, full of advice"
  38,2,But the unbelievers are steeped in self-glory and separatism
  38,3,"How many generations before them did We destroy? In the end they cried, when there was no longer time for being saved"
  38,4,"So they wonder how a warner has come to them from among themselves, and the unbelievers say, “This is a deceiver telling lies"
  38,5,“Has he made the gods all into one God? Truly this is a curious thing.”
  38,6,"And the leader among them walks away saying, “Walk away, and remain constant to your gods, for this is truly a thing created"
  38,7,“We never heard the likes of this among the people of these latter days. This is nothing but a fabrication.”
  38,8,"“What, has the message been sent to him, of all people?” But they are in doubt concerning My message. No, they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Or have they the treasures of the mercy of your Lord, the Exalted in Power, and the Grantor of bounties without measure"
  38,10,"Or have they control of the heavens and the earth and all between? If so, let them ascend by means to reach that end"
  38,11,Soldiers there will be defeated among the companies
  38,12,Before them the people rejected Noah and ‘Ad. And Pharaoh the lord of stakes
  38,13,"And Thamud, the people of Lot, and the Companions of the Wood, these were the confederates"
  38,14,"Not one of them failed to reject the messengers, so My punishment came justly and inevitably"
  38,15,"They must only wait for a single mighty blast, and there will be no delay"
  38,16,"They say, “Our Lord, hasten to us our sentence before the Day of Account.”"
  38,17,"Have patience with what they say, and remember our servant David, the possessor of strength, for he constantly turned to God"
  38,18,"It was We Who made the hills declare in unison with him, Our praises in the evening and in the morning"
  38,19,"Then the birds gathered, and all turned with him to God"
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingdom, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment in speech and decision"
  38,21,"Has the story of the litigants reached you? Behold, they climbed over the wall of the private chamber"
  38,22,"Then they entered the presence of David, and he was terrified of them. They said, “Fear not, we are two litigants, one of whom has wronged the other. Now decide between us with truth, and treat us not with injustice, but guide us to the balanced way"
  38,23,"“This person is my brother. He has nine and ninety ewes, and I have one. Yet he says, ‘commit her to my care’, and is harsh to me in speech.”"
  38,24,"David said, “He has undoubtedly wronged you in demanding your ewe to be added to his ewes. Truly many are the partners who wrong each other. Not so do those who believe and do deeds of righteousness, they are but a few.” Then David realized that We had tried him. He asked forgiveness of his Lord, fell down bowing, and turned to God in repentance"
  38,25,"So We forgave him. He indeed approached Us, and this is a beautiful place of return"
  38,26,"O David, We indeed made you a creation of free will on the earth. So judge between people in truth, and do not follow your desires, for they will mislead you from the path of God. Those who wander astray from the path of God is a terrible penalty, because they forget the Day of Account"
  38,27,"Not without purpose did We create heaven and earth, and all between. That was the thought of the unbelievers, but woe to the unbelievers, because of the fire of hell"
  38,28,"Shall We treat those who believe and do deeds of righteousness, the same as those who do wrong on the earth? Shall We treat those who guard against wrong, the same as those who turn away from right"
  38,29,"Here is a book which We have sent down to you, full of blessings, that they may think on its signs, and that people of understanding may receive the advice"
  38,30,"To David We gave Solomon, excellent in Our service, and he constantly turned to Us"
  38,31,"Behold, there were brought before him, in the evening, excellently bred horses"
  38,32,"And he said, “I truly love the love of excellence, with the remembrance of my Guardian Evolver.” Until they were hidden in the veil"
  38,33,“Bring them back to me.” Then he began to pass his hand over their legs and their necks
  38,34,"And We tried Solomon. We placed on his throne a body, but he turned to Us"
  38,35,"He said, “O my Lord, forgive me, and grant me a kingdom that will not suit another after me, for You are the Grantor of Bounties"
  38,36,"Then We subjected the wind to his power, to flow gently to his order, wherever he willed"
  38,37,"And the devils, every kind of builder and diver"
  38,38,And others bound in chains
  38,39,"“Such are Our bounties, whether you bestow them or withhold them, no account will be asked.”"
  38,40,"And he indeed enjoyed a near approach to Us, and a beautiful place of return"
  38,41,"Remember Our servant Job. Behold, he cried to his Lord, “Satan has afflicted me with distress and suffering.”"
  38,42,"“Strike here with your foot, here is water with which to wash, cool and refreshing, and to drink.”"
  38,43,"And We gave him back to his people, and doubled their number, as a grace from Us, and a thing for commemoration, for all who have understanding"
  38,44,"“And take in your hand a little grass, and bend it, but do not break it.” Truly We found him full of patience and constancy, and how excellent he was in Our service, and he constantly turned to Us"
  38,45,"And commemorate Our servants Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, all were possessors of power and vision"
  38,46,"Indeed We choose them for a special purpose, proclaiming the message of the hereafter"
  38,47,"They were, in Our sight, truly of the company of the elect, the best"
  38,48,"And remember Ishmael, Elisha, and Zul-Kifl. Each of them was of the company of the best"
  38,49,"This is indeed a reminder that indeed for the righteous, there is a beautiful place of return"
  38,50,"Gardens of eternity, whose doors will be open to them"
  38,51,"They will recline therein. Therein they can call for fruit in abundance, and drink"
  38,52,"And beside them will be chaste women restraining their glances, companions of equal age"
  38,53,Such is the promise made to you for the Day of Account
  38,54,Truly such will be Our bounty and it will never fail
  38,55,"Yes, but for the wrongdoers will be a terrible place of return"
  38,56,"They will burn in hell, a miserable resting place indeed"
  38,57,"Yes, then will they taste a boiling fluid, and a fluid dark, murky, intensely cold"
  38,58,And other penalties of a similar kind to match them
  38,59,This is a company bursting in with you. No welcome is there for them. Certainly they will burn in the fire
  38,60,"They say, “No welcome for you. It is you who have brought this upon us. Miserable is this place to stay in.”"
  38,61,"They will say, “Our Lord, whoever brought this upon us, add to him a double penalty in the fire.”"
  38,62,"And they will say, “What has happened to us that we do not see the people who we used to number among the harmful"
  38,63,"“Did we treat them with ridicule, or have we failed to perceive them?”"
  38,64,"Truly that is just and fitting, the talk of people of the fire"
  38,65,"Say, “Truly I am a warner. No god is there but the one God, Supreme, and Irresistible"
  38,66,"“The Lord of the heavens and the earth, and all between, Exalted in Might, able to enforce His will, forgiving again and again.”"
  38,67,"Say, “That is a message supreme"
  38,68,“From which you turn away
  38,69,"“I have no knowledge of the leaders on high, when they discuss matters among themselves"
  38,70,"“Only this has been revealed to me, that I give warning plainly and publicly.”"
  38,71,"Behold, your Lord said to the angels, “I am about to create the human being from mud"
  38,72,"“When I have fashioned him and breathed into him of My spirit, fall down to him in prostration.”"
  38,73,"So the angels prostrated themselves, all of them together"
  38,74,"Except Lucifer. He was arrogant, and became one of those who reject"
  38,75,"God said, “O Lucifer, what prevents you from prostrating yourself to one who I have created with my two hands? Are you arrogant? Or are you one of the high and mighty ones?”"
  38,76,"Lucifer said, “I am better than he. You created me from fire, and him you created from mud.”"
  38,77,"God said, “Get out of here then, for you are rejected, accursed"
  38,78,“And My curse will be on you until the Day of Accountability.”
  38,79,"Lucifer said, “O my Lord, then give me respite, until the day they are raised.”"
  38,80,"God said, “Respite is granted you"
  38,81,“Until the day of the time appointed.”
  38,82,"Lucifer said, “Then by Your power, I will mislead them all"
  38,83,"“Except Your servants among them, sincere and purified.”"
  38,84,"God said, “Then it is just and fitting, and I say only what is just and fitting"
  38,85,"“That I will certainly fill hell with you and those who follow you, all of them.”"
  38,86,"Say, “No reward do I ask of you for this, nor am I a pretender"
  38,87,“This is no less than a message for all the systems of knowledge
  38,88,"“And you will certainly know the truth of it all, in due time.”"
  39,1,"The revelation of this Book is from God, the Exalted in Power, Full of Wisdom"
  39,2,"Indeed it is We Who have revealed the Book to you in truth. So serve God, offering Him sincere devotion"
  39,3,"Is it not to God that sincere devotion is due? But those who take for protectors other than God say, “We only serve them in order that they may bring us nearer to God.” Truly God will judge between them in that which they differ, but God does not guide those who are false and ungrateful"
  39,4,"Had God wished to take for Himself a son, He could have chosen whom He pleased out of those whom He creates, but glory is to Him. He is God, the One, the Irresistible"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth in true proportion. He makes the night overlap the day, and the day overlap the night. He has subjected the Sun and the Moon, each one follows a course for a time appointed. Is He not the Exalted in Power? Does He not forgive again and again"
  39,6,"He created you all from a single soul. Then created of like nature her mate. And He sent down for you eight heads of livestock in pairs. He creates you in the wombs of your mothers, in stages one after another, in three veils of darkness. Such is God, your Lord. To Him belongs all control. There is no god but He. Then how are you turned away"
  39,7,"If you reject God, truly God has no need of you, but He likes not ingratitude from His servants. If you are grateful, He is pleased with you. No bearer of burdens can bear the burden of another. In the end, to your Lord is your return, then He will tell you the truth of all that you did, for He knows well all that is in the heart"
  39,8,"When some trouble touches the people, they cry to their Lord, turning to Him in repentance, but when He bestows a favor upon them as from Himself, the people forget that they ever cried and prayed, and they set up rivals to God, misleading others from God's path. Say, “Enjoy your blasphemy for a little while, indeed you are of the companions of the fire.”"
  39,9,"Is one who worships devoutly during the hours of the night, prostrating himself and standing, who is aware of the hereafter, and who places his hope in the mercy of his Lord like one who does not? Say, “Are those equal, those who know and those who do not know? It is those who are endued with understanding that remember.”"
  39,10,"Say, “O my servants who believe, be conscious of your Guardian Evolver, good is for those who do good in the present, and it will be as spacious as God's earth. Those who patiently persevere will truly receive a reward without measure.”"
  39,11,"Say, “Indeed I am asked to serve God with sincere devotion"
  39,12,“And I am asked to be the first of those who bow to God in religion.”
  39,13,"Say, “Indeed I fear, if I ignore my Guardian Evolver, the penalty of a mighty day.”"
  39,14,"Say, “It is God I serve with sincere devotion"
  39,15,"“Serve what you will besides Him.” Say, “Those who are indeed lost, are those who lose their souls and their people on the Day of Accountability. That is indeed an evident loss"
  39,16,"They will have layers of fire above them, and layers of fire below them. With this does God warn his servants, “O My servants, be conscious of Me.”"
  39,17,"Those who avoid wrong, and do not fall into its worship, and turn to God, for them is good news. So announce the good news to My servants"
  39,18,"Those who listen to the word, and adhere to the best of it. Those are the ones who God has guided, and those are the ones endowed with understanding"
  39,19,"Then is one against whom the decree of punishment is justly due, equal to one who avoids wrong? Can you then save one who is in the fire"
  39,20,"But for those who are conscious of their Lord are lofty mansions, one above another, built high. Beneath them rivers flow. Such is the promise of God. Never does God fail in His promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see that God sends down rain from the sky, and leads it through springs in the earth? Then He causes to grow there, produce of various colors. Then it withers. You will see it grow yellow. Then He makes it dry up and crumble away. Truly in this is a message of remembrance to people of understanding"
  39,22,"Is one whose heart God has opened to Al-Islam, so that he has received enlightenment from God, no better than one hard-hearted? Woe to those whose hearts are hardened against celebrating the praises of God. They are clearly in error"
  39,23,"God has revealed the best hadith, a book consistent with itself, repeating. The skin of those who fear their Lord shivers from it. Then their skin and their hearts soften to the celebration of God's praises. Such is the guidance of God. He guides with it whom He pleases, but those who God leaves to stray, can have none to guide"
  39,24,"Is then one who has to fear the brunt of the penalty on the Day of Accountability on his face, like one guarded from it? It will be said to the wrongdoers, “Taste of what you earned.”"
  39,25,"Those before them also rejected it, and so the punishment came to them from directions they did not perceive"
  39,26,"So God gave them a taste of humiliation in the present life, but greater is the punishment of the hereafter, if they only knew"
  39,27,"We have put forth for humanity in this Quran, every kind of parable, in order that they may receive advice"
  39,28,"A Quran in Arabic, without anything out-of-place, in order that they may guard against wrong"
  39,29,"God puts forth a parable of a person belonging to many partners at odds with each other, and a person belonging entirely to one man. Are those two equal in comparison? Praise God, but most of them do not understand"
  39,30,"Truly you will die, and truly they will die"
  39,31,"In the end will you all, on the Day of Accountability, settle your disputes in the presence of your Lord. 31 (End of Part)"